<div id="main">
	<div class="entry">

		<h1>RSVP to the UK Wedding</h1>
		<p>Thanks for RSVPing online! We want to keep in touch with everyone regarding the wedding, particularly as we will only have menu choices available nearer to the date and we need to follow up with each guest regarding their menu choice. This is a custom written application so it may have a few bugs. If it does, contact us (using the contact) and we'll take your RSVP by hand and also look at the problem.</p>
		<h2>Your RSVP Card</h2>
	<p>Your RSVP card should have two sections: guests' names and a PIN number:</p>
	<!-- image in frame -->
    <div class="frame_box frame_big">
   	  	<%= image_tag("RSVP-card.png") %>
        <span class="img_tl"></span><span class="img_tr"></span><span class="img_bl"></span><span class="img_br"></span>
    </div>
    <!--/ image in frame -->
	</div>


	


	<div class="comment-form">
		<%= form_for @guest, :url => login_path do |f| %>
			<%= content_tag :p, flash[:error], :style => 'color: red;' if flash[:error] %>
			<h2>Name</h2>
			<p>Please enter your surname, as written on the invitation. If the guests named on your invitation have different surnames, use the first surname. For example if the RSVP says: &ldquo;Jack Bucket and Jill Hill&rdquo;, then please use &ldquo;Bucket&rdquo;.</p>
			<div class="row">
				<%= f.label :last_name, 'Surname' %>
				<%= f.text_field :last_name, :class => 'text_field_verify', :size => 12 %>
			</div>
			
			<h2>PIN</h2>
			<p>Enter the four digit PIN number on the RSVP card.</p>
			<div class="row">
				<%= f.label :pin, 'PIN' %>
				<%= f.text_field :pin, :class => 'text_field_pin', :size => 4 %>
			</div>
					
			<div class="row"><%= f.submit 'Start RSVP', :class => 'btn-submit' %></div>
		<% end %>
	</div>
</div>